KWIC (keywords-in-context)

tweets <- read_csv("https://curiositybits.cc/files/metoo.csv")
corpus1 <- corpus(tweets,docid_field = "status_id",text_field = "text")  ## use the 'status_id' column as unique identifiers of documents 
data_tokens <- tokens(corpus1)

kw <- kwic(data_tokens, pattern =  "victim*") 
head(kw, 10) # SHOW 10 RECORDS OF DOCUMENTS THAT CONTAIN WORDS BEGINNING WITH 'KILL'

TF-IDF

rank words by term frequency

tweets_dfm <- tokens(corpus1, remove_punct = TRUE, remove_numbers = TRUE, remove_symbols = TRUE, remove_url=TRUE) %>%  
  tokens_remove(stopwords("en")) %>%
  dfm()

topfeatures(tweets_dfm) ## this shows top words by basic word count
##   #metoo movement    women      amp       de roseanne   sexual     just 
##     4956      586      464      447      331      329      313      259 
##     like     barr 
##      257      244

rank words by TF-IDF

tweets_dfm <- dfm_tfidf(tweets_dfm) #create a new DFM by tf-idf scores
topfeatures(tweets_dfm) ## this shows top words by tf-idf
## movement      amp    women       de roseanne   sexual       の     like 
## 555.0922 537.1178 508.2615 466.2138 396.2413 392.1675 368.5139 341.6351 
##     just     barr 
## 340.0487 323.0041

Keyness (an alternative to tf-idf)

tweets_dfm <- tokens(corpus1, remove_punct = TRUE, remove_numbers = TRUE, remove_symbols = TRUE, remove_url=TRUE) %>%
  dfm() %>%
  dfm_group(groups = is_quote)  ## group the corpus by unique values in the is_quote column

key <- textstat_keyness(tweets_dfm)
textplot_keyness(key)

Semantic network

Create a DFM that contains hashtags and get top 50 hashtags in the DFM

tag_dfm <- dfm_select(tweets_dfm, pattern = "#*")
toptag <- names(topfeatures(tag_dfm, 50)) # get top 50 results
head(toptag)
## [1] "#metoo"            "#timesup"          "#feminism"        
## [4] "#maga"             "#leavingneverland" "#metoo⁠"

Construct feature-occurrence matrix of hashtags

tag_fcm <- fcm(tag_dfm)

Visualize the semantic network based on hashtag co-occurrence

topgat_fcm <- fcm_select(tag_fcm, pattern = toptag)
textplot_network(topgat_fcm, min_freq = 0.1, edge_alpha = 0.5, edge_size = 1, edge_color = "orange")

LDA Topic models

tmod_lda <- textmodel_lda(tweets_dfm, k = 20) # Set k=10 and look for 20 topics in the dfm.
